"Brown K., Tegoni M., Prudêncio M., Pereira A.S., Besson S., Moura J.J., Moura I., Cambillau C.","A novel type of catalytic copper cluster in nitrous oxide reductase",2000,"Nature Structural Biology","7","3",,"191","195",,,10.1038/73288,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0034049124&partnerID=40&md5=53be5659f61a7432213fab09cf1ffd1f","Architecture et Fonction des Macromolécules Biologiques, UPR 9039, CNRS, 31 Chemin Joseph Aiguier, 13402 Marseille Cedex 20, France; Departamento de Química, Centro de Química Fina e Biotecnologia, Universidade Nova de Lisboa, 2825 Monte de Caparica, Portugal","Brown, K., Architecture et Fonction des Macromolécules Biologiques, UPR 9039, CNRS, 31 Chemin Joseph Aiguier, 13402 Marseille Cedex 20, France; Tegoni, M., Architecture et Fonction des Macromolécules Biologiques, UPR 9039, CNRS, 31 Chemin Joseph Aiguier, 13402 Marseille Cedex 20, France; Prudêncio, M., Departamento de Química, Centro de Química Fina e Biotecnologia, Universidade Nova de Lisboa, 2825 Monte de Caparica, Portugal; Pereira, A.S., Departamento de Química, Centro de Química Fina e Biotecnologia, Universidade Nova de Lisboa, 2825 Monte de Caparica, Portugal; Besson, S., Departamento de Química, Centro de Química Fina e Biotecnologia, Universidade Nova de Lisboa, 2825 Monte de Caparica, Portugal; Moura, J.J., Departamento de Química, Centro de Química Fina e Biotecnologia, Universidade Nova de Lisboa, 2825 Monte de Caparica, Portugal; Moura, I., Departamento de Química, Centro de Química Fina e Biotecnologia, Universidade Nova de Lisboa, 2825 Monte de Caparica, Portugal; Cambillau, C., Architecture et Fonction des Macromolécules Biologiques, UPR 9039, CNRS, 31 Chemin Joseph Aiguier, 13402 Marseille Cedex 20, France","Nitrous oxide (N2O) is a greenhouse gas, the third most significant contributor to global warming. As a key process for N2O elimination from the biosphere, N2O reductases catalyze the two-electron reduction of N2O to N2. These 2 x 65 kDa copper enzymes are thought to contain a CuA electron entry site, similar to that of cytochrome c oxidase, and a CuZ catalytic center. The copper anomalous signal was used to solve the crystal structure of N2O reductase from Pseudomonas nautica by multiwavelength anomalous dispersion, to a resolution of 2.4 Å. The structure reveals that the CuZ center belongs to a new type of metal cluster, in which four copper ions are liganded by seven histidine residues. N2O binds to this center via a single copper ion. The remaining copper ions might act as an electron reservoir, assuring a fast electron transfer and avoiding the formation of dead-end products.",,"copper; cytochrome c oxidase; nitrous oxide; nitrous oxide reductase; anaerobic metabolism; article; crystal structure; electron transport; enzyme activity; enzyme analysis; enzyme structure; priority journal; protein domain; Pseudomonas; reduction; structure analysis; Amino Acid Sequence; Azurin; Binding Sites; Catalytic Domain; Copper; Crystallography, X-Ray; Dimerization; Histidine; Hydrogen Bonding; Models, Molecular; Molecular Sequence Data; Nitrous Oxide; Oxidation-Reduction; Oxidoreductases; Protein Conformation; Protein Folding; Pseudomonas; Structure-Activity Relationship; Bacteria (microorganisms); Marinobacter hydrocarbonoclasticus; Negibacteria; Pseudomonas",,"Azurin, 12284-43-4; Copper, 7440-50-8; cupredoxin; Histidine, 71-00-1; nitrous oxide reductase, EC 1.7.99.6; Nitrous Oxide, 10024-97-2; Oxidoreductases, EC 1.-",,,,,"Cambillau, C.; Arch. Fonction Macromolec. des Biol., UPR 9039, CNRS, 31 Chemin Joseph Aiguier, 13402 Marseille CEDEX 20, France; email: cambillau@afmb.cnrs-mrs.fr",,,,,,,,10728368,,NSBIE,10700275,"English","Nat. Struct. Biol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0034049124
